==Singlish==
===Etymology===
From [[Min Nan]] ([[驚死]], [[惊死]] POJ: kiaⁿ-sí); literally: "afraid to die"

===Noun===
'''kiasi'''
# (colloquial) (derogatory) a coward
#:Why are you so Kiasi? You won't die from getting a small cut on the finger.
# (colloquial) (derogatory) a nickname
#:He is such a Kiasi, he does not have the guts to take a chance at anything.

